        jTextArea2.setText("------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nINTEGER\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   INTEGER declaration is used to define numeric variables holding whole \n   numbers.\n\n\tSyntax\n\t\tINTEGER a=1\n\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  +\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\t'+' operator adds two declared integers\n\n\tSyntax\n\t\tINTEGER a=1\n\t\tINTEGER b=2\n\t\tINTEGER c=0\n\t\tc=a+b \n\t\tPRINT c \n\t\tEND\t// prints 3\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  -\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\t'-' operator substract two declared integers\n\n\tSyntax\n\t\tINTEGER a=2\n\t\tINTEGER b=1\n\t\tINTEGER c=0\n\t\tc=a-b \n\t\tPRINT c \n\t\tEND\t// prints 1\n\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n <\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  < is equivalent to \"less than”. < operator is used to compare if the first \ndeclared integer is less than the second. \n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n ==\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  == is equivalent to \"equal to”, IEQ operator is used to compare if the 2 \ndeclared integers is equal. If the program’s output is equal to 1 then the 2 \nintegers is equal and if 0 then it is not equal.\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  PRINT\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  PRINT function prints string literal or variable value after instruction \ndeclaration.\n\n  Syntax:\n\tINTEGER c=1 \n\tPRINT c\n\tEND\t\t\t\t\t//print 1\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  END\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \n  END statement is used to terminate the program.\n\t\n  Syntax:\n\tINTEGER C=1\n\tEND\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   CONDITIONAL STATEMENTS (IF AND ELSEIF)\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   IF and ELSEIF requires conditional statement after instruction declaration.\n\n   Syntax:\n\tINTEGER A=1\n\tINTEGER B=1\n\tINTEGER C=0\n\tIF A<=B \n\tTHEN C=1\n\tENDIF\n\tPRINT C\t\t\t//prints 1\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   ENDIF\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   ENDIF is used to terminate IF statement.\n\n   Syntax:\n\tIF A<=B \n\tTHEN C=1\n\tENDIF\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   THEN\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\tTHEN is used after IF statement.\n\n   Syntax:\n\tIF A<=B \n\tTHEN C=1\n\tENDIF\n\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   WHILE\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    WHILE requires a conditional statement after declaration, then proceeds the\n    executable statements. Remember to include an iterator of the variable being\n    compared in the condition or your code will produce an infinite loop result.\n\n    Syntax:\n\tINTEGER c=1\n\tWHILE c<3\n\t    PRINT c\n\t    c=c+1\n\tENDLOOP\n\tEND\t\t\t//prints \"1 2\"\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   ENDLOOP\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   ENDLOOP is used to terminate WHILE statement.\n\n  Syntax:\n\tWHILE C<3\n\t    c=c+1\n\tENDLOOP\n\t\t\n");
